@node Install

    If you woant save the Pictures, the volume must be writeabel.
    (A CD-Rom isn`t writeabel.)

    Also, copy the MahJong Drawer on your Harddisk.

@endnode

@node Olala

    The background pic can be replaced, max. 7 bitplanes, 
    highres is needed.

@endnode


@node laden


   Press load and push in one of the 20 Buttons, a filerequester
   will open. Chose your pic. 

   Those preferences must be kept:


   1.) Pal Hires.
   2.) Max 128 colores. (less is fine)
   3.) Solution 640x256 Pixel.

   If something is wrong you get a Message.

   Create or manipulate a picture, keep the preference in mind an go
   ahead.   

   Load and save with PicEd.

@endnode

@node zeige

  Is a pic been loaded, you can use the Button "Show", to controlle
  if it is really your pic.

@endnode

@node dragon

  To see, how the Picture looks like, with a Dragon, push the
  Button "Show Dragon".
  So you can see, how the Colours (Pic and Dragon) harmonize.

@endnode
 

@node save

  Here you can save! The oldone will be overwritten, please make sure
  to have a copy of it. 

  To keep the old pics, show in the path Mahjong/hp (backgroundpics)
  with the names Pic1 - Pic20. Each pic has also a file with the name
  p1.... till p20. For exeample you want to save pic7 then you have 
  to save p7 also.  

  It is save to have a copy of these drawer somewhere :-)

@endnode


